      • getValuesForArg

        <O> Collection<O> getValuesForArg(Object arg1,
                                  Object arg2,
                                  Context ctx)
        Gets all facts for the binary predicate based on arg pattern. It takes an arg1 and an arg2, but expects exactly one of them to be null. It then finds all facts for the predicate that have arg1 or arg2 (the non-null arg) as visible from ctx, and returns as O objects based on the null argument position of the facts. For example, assuming you had KbObjects for the BinaryPredicate isa and the individual Plato, this: isa.getValuesForArg(plato, null, inferencePSC); Would be equivalent to the following query: (isa Plato ?COL) in InferencePSC ... and would return all of the Collections to which Plato belongs, as visible from InferencePSC.
